U.S. tax increases and spending
cuts set for the beginning of next year may be averted by
lawmakers in Washington,  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS) ’s chief U.S.
equity strategist  David Kostin  said.  “This is unlikely to be resolved in a smooth fashion,”
Kostin said today at a conference in San Diego sponsored by the
Insured Retirement Institute. The fiscal cliff will probably
will be resolved in a “messy way,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
